00:40:26,545 --> 00:40:27,587
Hello?

1002
00:40:27,671 --> 00:40:29,047
I've heard absolutely
nothing from your father

1003
00:40:29,131 --> 00:40:30,340
and I'm going insane.

1004
00:40:30,424 --> 00:40:31,466
Then you'll fit right into our family.

1005
00:40:31,550 --> 00:40:32,801
<i>What could possibly be the holdup?</i>

1006
00:40:32,885 --> 00:40:34,511
I'm a doctor.
Do you know what kind of parking spaces

1007
00:40:34,595 --> 00:40:36,263
you get when you're a doctor?
Spectacular.

1008
00:40:36,347 --> 00:40:37,431
That was the clincher for me.

1009
00:40:37,515 --> 00:40:39,016
<i>I wonder if I blew it
with my reading list.</i>

1010
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:41,268
-Why?
-I padded it a little.

1011
00:40:41,352 --> 00:40:42,853
A lot. I padded it a lot.

1012
00:40:42,937 --> 00:40:44,604
<i>-It doesn't matter.</i>
-What if there's a quiz?

1013
00:40:44,688 --> 00:40:46,606
-There won't be a quiz.
-We had fun, didn't we?

1014
00:40:46,690 --> 00:40:48,860
Hey, relax. You have surgery today.

1015
00:40:48,944 --> 00:40:51,237
Go have a martini.
Or you're in a hospital, take a Seconal.

1016
00:40:51,321 --> 00:40:52,572
Someday I'll need to explain to you

1017
00:40:52,656 --> 00:40:54,115
what surgery actually entails.

1018
00:40:54,199 --> 00:40:55,867
-MAN [ON PA]: <i>Paging Dr. Ettenberg.</i>
-Maybe I should call him again.

1019
00:40:55,951 --> 00:40:58,411
<i>-Is that too desperate?</i>
-Do you have to go?

1020
00:40:58,495 --> 00:40:59,746
<i>No. Why?</i>

1021
00:40:59,830 --> 00:41:01,789
-Aren't you Dr. Ettenberg?
-Yeah, so?

1022
00:41:01,873 --> 00:41:03,374
Oh, God, I have to go.
I told you, insane.

1023
00:41:03,458 --> 00:41:05,418
-I'll call you later.
-It's all going to be fine.

1024
00:41:05,502 --> 00:41:06,878
I promise you.

1025
00:41:06,962 --> 00:41:08,921
[PHONE RINGS]

1026
00:41:09,005 --> 00:41:10,256
Hello?

1027
00:41:10,340 --> 00:41:11,966
SHY [OVER PHONE]: <i>May
I speak to Mrs. Maisel?</i>

1028
00:41:12,050 --> 00:41:13,384
Who's calling?

1029
00:41:13,468 --> 00:41:14,969
Shy Baldwin here.

1030
00:41:15,053 --> 00:41:16,512
We met the other night, remember?

1031
00:41:16,596 --> 00:41:19,098
Remember? Well… Shy Baldwin?

1032
00:41:19,182 --> 00:41:21,392
Shy… Mama!

1033
00:41:21,476 --> 00:41:23,394
My mother would love to talk to…
Mama, seriously!

1034
00:41:23,478 --> 00:41:26,105
Oh, shit, I forgot. Hairdresser.

1035
00:41:26,189 --> 00:41:27,523
Hairdresser's very important.

1036
00:41:27,607 --> 00:41:29,150
<i>She will never forgive
me if she misses this.</i>

1037
00:41:29,234 --> 00:41:30,360
She will kill me. Brutally.

1038
00:41:30,444 --> 00:41:31,527
And then it might be
linked to you in the press

1039
00:41:31,611 --> 00:41:32,695
and I'd feel terrible about that.
Please wait

1040
00:41:32,779 --> 00:41:34,073
till she gets back.
Can I get you some coffee?

1041
00:41:34,157 --> 00:41:35,991
Absolutely, cream and sugar.

1042
00:41:36,075 --> 00:41:38,077
-You're not here.
<i>-And you should be a singer</i>

1043
00:41:38,161 --> 00:41:39,328
with that kind of breath control.

1044
00:41:39,412 --> 00:41:40,537
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

1045
00:41:40,621 --> 00:41:43,040
I'm just a really big…
Why are you calling?

1046
00:41:43,124 --> 00:41:45,501
<i>Because I saw you on that telethon</i>

1047
00:41:45,585 --> 00:41:47,878
<i>and I thought you were sensational.</i>

1048
00:41:47,962 --> 00:41:49,880
And as I was sitting
there having my nightcap,

1049
00:41:49,964 --> 00:41:53,509
I said to myself, "Why
isn't that girl a star?"

1050
00:41:53,593 --> 00:41:55,552
<i>And then I said to myself,
"Well, you know what, Shy,</i>

1051
00:41:55,636 --> 00:41:57,304
<i>you can help with this situation."</i>

1052
00:41:57,388 --> 00:41:59,473
So I am.

1053
00:41:59,557 --> 00:42:02,434
How would you like
to open for me on tour?

1054
00:42:02,518 --> 00:42:03,811
What?

1055
00:42:03,895 --> 00:42:05,104
<i>It'll be six months.</i>

1056
00:42:05,188 --> 00:42:06,605
<i>Three in the States, three in Europe.</i>

1057
00:42:06,689 --> 00:42:09,691
<i>You'll do 30 minutes and
a couple of bits with me.</i>

1058
00:42:09,775 --> 00:42:11,402
<i>We leave in two weeks and you'll need</i>

1059
00:42:11,486 --> 00:42:13,946
<i>a lot of new fancy
clothes, which I will pay for.</i>

1060
00:42:14,030 --> 00:42:16,698
<i>There it is.
That's the purpose of my phone call.</i>

1061
00:42:16,782 --> 00:42:18,158
<i>-So, what do you…</i>
-Yes.

1062
00:42:18,242 --> 00:42:21,413
Are you sure you don't need… No. Yes.

1063
00:42:21,497 --> 00:42:23,164
Oh, my God. Yes.

1064
00:42:23,248 --> 00:42:25,625
<i>Then we have a deal, Little Miss Mouthy.</i>

1065
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:28,420
<i>I'll get in touch with your
people to work out the details.</i>

1066
00:42:28,504 --> 00:42:30,255
We're gonna have a hell of a time.

1067
00:42:30,339 --> 00:42:31,548
<i>Talk to you soon.</i>

1068
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,264
[SCREAMS]

1069
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:43,894
[PANTING]

1070
00:42:46,522 --> 00:42:48,231
Oh!

1071
00:42:48,315 --> 00:42:49,691
I have news.

1072
00:42:49,775 --> 00:42:51,734
God, give me a fucking heart attack.

1073
00:42:51,818 --> 00:42:54,446
Wait, the heart attack's coming.
We need a drink.

1074
00:42:54,530 --> 00:42:55,697
I need a defibrillator.

1075
00:42:55,781 --> 00:42:57,532
-You ready?
-Sure.

1076
00:42:57,616 --> 00:42:59,409
You are gonna have to give
me a better "sure" than that.

1077
00:42:59,493 --> 00:43:02,120
-Sure!
-Ew, go back.

1078
00:43:02,204 --> 00:43:03,455
Just fucking say it.

1079
00:43:07,335 --> 00:43:10,087
We are going on tour with Shy Baldwin.

1080
00:43:10,171 --> 00:43:11,464
What?

1081
00:43:11,548 --> 00:43:13,340
He saw me at the telethon in my shit spot

1082
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:16,802
and he loved me and he wants
me to open for him for six months.

1083
00:43:16,886 --> 00:43:19,305
Huh?
How's that story gonna play on Jack Paar?

1084
00:43:19,389 --> 00:43:21,390
-You're sure it was Shy Baldwin?
-Yup.

1085
00:43:21,474 --> 00:43:23,058
And you're sure he asked you to tour,

1086
00:43:23,142 --> 00:43:24,059
like flat-out asked you?

1087
00:43:24,143 --> 00:43:25,060
I want a pink dressing room.

1088
00:43:25,144 --> 00:43:26,187
Can you put that in my contract?

1089
00:43:26,271 --> 00:43:27,646
You're gonna open for Shy Baldwin.

1090
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:29,732
Fuck Midtown, we're going to Europe.

1091
00:43:29,816 --> 00:43:31,066
I'm gonna need a passport.

1092
00:43:31,150 --> 00:43:32,401
And some decent underwear.

1093
00:43:32,485 --> 00:43:33,944
I can't believe it.

1094
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:35,154
You know what I'd love to do?

1095
00:43:35,238 --> 00:43:37,823
Buy Sophie Lennon some flowers.

1096
00:43:37,907 --> 00:43:39,575
Sophie Lennon?

1097
00:43:39,659 --> 00:43:41,785
If she hadn't bumped me, I
never would've gone on at midnight

1098
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:44,121
and Shy never would have seen
me and I wouldn't be assembling

1099
00:43:44,205 --> 00:43:45,539
a fabulous traveling
outfit in my head right now.

1100
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:47,458
I see a blue hat with feathers.

1101
00:43:47,542 --> 00:43:48,959
Let's just focus on the tour.

1102
00:43:49,043 --> 00:43:51,629
Revenge is a dish best served cold.

1103
00:43:51,713 --> 00:43:53,798
Get ready for some ice cream, bitch.

1104
00:43:53,882 --> 00:43:55,091
I should get his people on the phone.

1105
00:43:55,175 --> 00:43:57,052
Start talking salary; I
don't want him thinking

1106
00:43:57,136 --> 00:43:58,428
just 'cause you're new, you're cheap.

1107
00:43:58,512 --> 00:44:01,264
I am totally new and completely cheap.

1108
00:44:01,348 --> 00:44:03,267
Hey, hey.

1109
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:08,981
We did it. You and me.

1110
00:44:10,983 --> 00:44:13,068
Miriam, I should tell you something.

1111
00:44:13,152 --> 00:44:14,236
-You love me.
-No.

1112
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:15,362
I am amazing.

1113
00:44:15,446 --> 00:44:17,113
Can you please stop
talking about yourself?

1114
00:44:17,197 --> 00:44:18,865
That's our bread and butter now, sister.

1115
00:44:18,949 --> 00:44:20,825
I just need to tell you…

1116
00:44:20,909 --> 00:44:23,411
My underwear's fine, so shut up.

1117
00:44:23,495 --> 00:44:25,163
We're going shopping.

1118
00:44:25,247 --> 00:44:26,623
Right now.

1119
00:44:26,707 --> 00:44:29,834
I have dresses to buy and hats to buy

1120
00:44:29,918 --> 00:44:32,254
and shoes to buy and purses to buy.

1121
00:44:32,338 --> 00:44:34,256
Should we maybe make
some money before we go broke

1122
00:44:34,340 --> 00:44:37,968
and have to blow job
our way across Europe?

1123
00:44:38,052 --> 00:44:39,511
[EXHALES]

1124
00:44:40,597 --> 00:44:43,140
Hello? It's me. Who's here?

1125
00:44:43,224 --> 00:44:44,809
ABE: Miriam. I need to talk to you.

1126
00:44:44,893 --> 00:44:46,227
-[DOOR SLAMS]
-Can you do it on the move?

1127
00:44:46,311 --> 00:44:47,728
-I'm late.
-Of course you're late.

1128
00:44:47,812 --> 00:44:48,813
You're always late.

1129
00:44:48,897 --> 00:44:49,939
You ever wondered to yourself,

1130
00:44:50,023 --> 00:44:51,774
-"Why am I always late?"
-No.

1131
00:44:51,858 --> 00:44:53,818
Perhaps if you had a
watch for every outfit.

1132
00:44:53,902 --> 00:44:57,071
-You needed to talk to me, Papa?
-Yes, I've made a decision.

1133
00:44:57,155 --> 00:44:58,281
About what?

1134
00:44:58,365 --> 00:45:00,408
What do you mean, "about what?"

1135
00:45:00,492 --> 00:45:03,578
How many decisions concerning
you am I making these days?

1136
00:45:03,662 --> 00:45:04,745
I don't know. Six?

1137
00:45:04,829 --> 00:45:06,122
-No.
-Eight?

1138
00:45:06,206 --> 00:45:07,415
-No.
-Thirty-five?

1139
00:45:07,499 --> 00:45:10,042
I made a decision
concerning you and Benjamin.

1140
00:45:10,126 --> 00:45:13,671
I know it took longer
than you had desired,

1141
00:45:13,755 --> 00:45:15,548
but I had a devil of a
time getting my hands

1142
00:45:15,632 --> 00:45:17,049
on his vaccination records.

1143
00:45:17,133 --> 00:45:19,677
I'm happy to say his
references checked out,

1144
00:45:19,761 --> 00:45:22,179
his financials are
sufficient, he can swim,

1145
00:45:22,263 --> 00:45:24,223
he's up-to-date on his mortgage payments,

1146
00:45:24,307 --> 00:45:26,643
his tax returns are in order,

1147
00:45:26,727 --> 00:45:29,813
and his patients have
an 86% survival rate.

1148
00:45:29,897 --> 00:45:32,316
I will admit his reading
list gave me pause.

1149
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:36,862
Panaslotsky is not a real
author and I was briefly offended

1150
00:45:36,946 --> 00:45:38,614
that he thought I could be duped.

1151
00:45:38,698 --> 00:45:42,200
However, after much deliberation, Miriam,

1152
00:45:42,284 --> 00:45:44,911
I have decided to give
Benjamin permission

1153
00:45:44,995 --> 00:45:46,830
to ask for your hand.

1154
00:45:46,914 --> 00:45:49,375
You may get married. Again.

1155
00:45:50,543 --> 00:45:54,922
What? What?

1156
00:45:56,507 --> 00:45:57,674
-Shit.
-[DOOR OPENS]

1157
00:45:57,758 --> 00:46:00,469
ROSE: Hello? Anyone here?

1158
00:46:00,553 --> 00:46:02,929
-Not a word. I'm coming, Rose.
-But Papa…

1159
00:46:03,013 --> 00:46:05,098
I have been waiting here
all day to tell your mother

1160
00:46:05,182 --> 00:46:06,975
some things that may well
make her take to her bed,

1161
00:46:07,059 --> 00:46:09,144
and I won't get a chance to
tell her those things if she's

1162
00:46:09,228 --> 00:46:10,646
-already taken to her bed.
-But…

1163
00:46:10,730 --> 00:46:12,732
Me first!

1164
00:46:14,401 --> 00:46:17,445
David Begelman says hello; I
ran into him at the shoe repair.

1165
00:46:17,529 --> 00:46:20,031
-He's aging very poorly.
-That's great.

1166
00:46:20,115 --> 00:46:23,826
Why don't we go into
my study for a minute?

1167
00:46:23,910 --> 00:46:25,244
-Okay.
-[SIGHS]

1168
00:46:25,328 --> 00:46:27,246
Just take a seat, please.

1169
00:46:27,330 --> 00:46:29,999
Um, where?

1170
00:46:30,083 --> 00:46:34,045
-Oh, uh…
-MIDGE: Mama?

1171
00:46:34,129 --> 00:46:35,755
-Uh…
-Papa?

1172
00:46:35,839 --> 00:46:39,050
-I'm late, I'm heading out!
-[DOOR OPENS]

1173
00:46:39,134 --> 00:46:41,260
Abe, please, what do
you want to talk about?

1174
00:46:41,344 --> 00:46:43,513
-Rose…
-[DOOR CLOSES]

1175
00:46:43,597 --> 00:46:44,847
You know that things have been

1176
00:46:44,931 --> 00:46:47,100
a little unsettled for me lately.

1177
00:46:47,184 --> 00:46:49,435
I know. They'll get better.

1178
00:46:49,519 --> 00:46:52,563
Yes, well, I went to Bell
Labs and talked to Charles.

1179
00:46:52,647 --> 00:46:54,774
-I was incredibly reasonable.
-Oh, dear.

1180
00:46:54,858 --> 00:46:56,609
-Is he hurt?
-No, Charles is fine.

1181
00:46:56,693 --> 00:46:58,403
We just talked.

1182
00:46:58,487 --> 00:47:01,865
But something happened
to me during that talk.

1183
00:47:01,949 --> 00:47:05,202
I started to think about my life.

1184
00:47:05,286 --> 00:47:08,414
Who I used to be, who I've become.

1185
00:47:08,498 --> 00:47:13,627
The choices I've made, the
way I've raised my children.

1186
00:47:13,711 --> 00:47:15,838
I think I need to reevaluate some things.

1187
00:47:15,922 --> 00:47:17,423
What things?

1188
00:47:17,507 --> 00:47:22,177
It's not going to work
out with Bell Labs, Rose.

1189
00:47:22,261 --> 00:47:24,346
That is not a place for me anymore.

1190
00:47:24,430 --> 00:47:27,349
Well, fine, you'll just
focus on the university.

1191
00:47:27,433 --> 00:47:29,226
And I'm going to leave Columbia.

1192
00:47:29,310 --> 00:47:30,561
What?

1193
00:47:30,645 --> 00:47:32,688
I don't want to teach there anymore.

1194
00:47:32,772 --> 00:47:34,064
But… But you're a tenured professor.

1195
00:47:34,148 --> 00:47:37,025
I know.
And they want to put me on the shelf.

1196
00:47:37,109 --> 00:47:39,069
-Take a sabbatical.
-A paid sabbatical.

1197
00:47:39,153 --> 00:47:41,613
I don't want their money
if I'm not earning it.

1198
00:47:41,697 --> 00:47:43,574
-Of course you do.
-I'm going to give it up.

1199
00:47:43,658 --> 00:47:44,908
All of it.

1200
00:47:44,992 --> 00:47:47,245
-The job, the tenure…
-You've lost your mind.

1201
00:47:47,329 --> 00:47:48,872
No, I haven't.

1202
00:47:48,956 --> 00:47:50,457
You're leaving Columbia?

1203
00:47:50,541 --> 00:47:53,376
I don't want to spend
my life just drifting along.

1204
00:47:53,460 --> 00:47:56,588
I used to have purpose. I want it back.

1205
00:47:56,672 --> 00:47:58,381
-You're giving up your tenure?
-Yes.

1206
00:47:58,465 --> 00:48:00,509
Colombia owns our apartment, Abe.

1207
00:48:05,264 --> 00:48:09,434
Yes… they do.

1208
00:48:09,518 --> 00:48:11,478
So, what do we do?

1209
00:48:11,562 --> 00:48:13,730
Move in with Miriam and Benjamin?

1210
00:48:20,529 --> 00:48:24,240
You'd really better sit down.

1211
00:48:24,324 --> 00:48:27,202
[APPLAUSE]

1212
00:48:27,286 --> 00:48:29,037
STEVE ALLEN: <i>So I'll tell you how we're</i>

1213
00:48:29,121 --> 00:48:31,039
<i>gonna fix the problem. We've decided</i>

1214
00:48:31,123 --> 00:48:32,958
that once a month, we
will book a comedian

1215
00:48:33,042 --> 00:48:34,168
-who will offend everyone.
-[LAUGHTER]

1216
00:48:34,252 --> 00:48:36,003
Fair enough? All right.

1217
00:48:36,087 --> 00:48:37,713
-MIDGE: He knows I'm coming.
-MAN: Doesn't matter.

1218
00:48:37,797 --> 00:48:39,381
-He knows I'm coming.
-You're not on the list.

1219
00:48:39,465 --> 00:48:40,841
-He knows I'm coming.
-He didn't leave a name.

1220
00:48:40,925 --> 00:48:42,384
He knows I'm coming. Lenny.

1221
00:48:42,468 --> 00:48:44,303
It's all right, Perry. She's my mother.

1222
00:48:44,387 --> 00:48:46,222
You didn't leave my name.
Perry's having a heart attack.

1223
00:48:46,306 --> 00:48:47,848
I'm very sorry, Perry.
It won't happen again.

1224
00:48:47,932 --> 00:48:49,433
People's names are
supposed to be on the list.

1225
00:48:49,517 --> 00:48:51,101
That's how it works.

1226
00:48:51,185 --> 00:48:53,145
There goes the next
president of the United States.

1227
00:48:53,229 --> 00:48:54,522
Never mind him. Let me look at you.

1228
00:48:54,606 --> 00:48:58,067
Good suit. Nice tie. Hair's fine.

1229
00:48:58,151 --> 00:49:01,070
Get ready for your intro.
Only he goes onstage.

1230
00:49:01,154 --> 00:49:03,322
Hmm, Perry knows
me better than I thought.

1231
00:49:03,406 --> 00:49:05,157
STEVE: Now, ladies and gentlemen,

1232
00:49:05,241 --> 00:49:06,992
here is a very shocking comedian,

1233
00:49:07,076 --> 00:49:09,036
the most shocking comedian of our time.

1234
00:49:09,120 --> 00:49:11,580
A young man who is skyrocketing to fame,

1235
00:49:11,664 --> 00:49:12,915
-Lenny Bruce.
-[CHEERING, APPLAUSE]

1236
00:49:12,999 --> 00:49:16,001
-Tits up.
-Thanks.

1237
00:49:16,085 --> 00:49:18,585
-You'll explain that when I get back?
-Yes, I will.

1238
00:49:28,432 --> 00:49:31,184
LENNY: Will Elizabeth
Taylor become bar mitzvahed?

1239
00:49:31,268 --> 00:49:32,644
[LAUGHTER]

